three sample summaries

[1] Angelica Dass insists that discrimination still exists all over the world, it does not disappear by itself. Thus, we have to try to work on for all people in the world to be equal. She was grown in a family with a variety of skin colors, so she knows that many people discriminate based on skin colors after going out into society. She felt dissatisfied with it, and started a movement to solve this problem. This movement is called Humanae that collects skin colors of people from different countries, ages, and backgrounds. She uses the Internet to spread this movement because many people see it, and share it. Humanae is useful for many people around the world, and they use it for various purposes. For example, art students use it to collect human face ideas for art activities.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   
[2] For a long time, the colour of our skin has been the first impression in the world. Angelica was born in a colourful skin colour family, so she does not have the meaning of skin colour. However, the colour of our skin has many meanings outside her home. She experienced that she was regarded by skin colour. For example, she was told not to use the main elevator when she went to her grandmothers house. Because, her skin colour can not belong somewhere. After she married Spanish men, she started projects Humanae as a photographer. Humanae is standing in front of white background and making it own skin colour background. Humanae spread from the internet to public space in the world, and 3,000 people from more than 90 countries joined the project. Humanae gives children who were told discriminatory things confidence. By the teacher, Humanae spread widely in the education fields. As a photographer, she realized that she can be a way of our communication. As Angelica, she feels sitting in front of a selapist when she takes a picture. In conclusion, discrimination does not disappear naturally, so we have to work on eliminating discrimination.
[3] She was talking about the tone of peoples skin. Although the discrimination has been abolished, we still live where the color of our skin not only gives a first impression, but a lasting one that remains. She has a lot of experiences being unfairly discriminated against because of skin color. So she has been trying to change the image of peoples skin color. Its name is Humanae which makes her a personal exercise as a photographer. Humanae is a pursuit to highlight our true colors rather than the untrue white, red, black or yellow associated with race. This action has a very big effect on our society. Many places and cases use this action to change the mind about discrimination of skin tone. For example, the art class in schools, colleges of art, exhibition in the art museum or the building in the town. She believes that the discrimination remains a common practice worldwide, and that will not disappear by itself.
